---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Taffy Town — Customer Story — Formic"
  description="Taffy Town eliminated lifting injuries and boosted efficiency with zero CapEx exposure."
  ogTitle="Taffy Town — Formic Customer Story"
  ogDescription="Eliminated lifting injuries · boosted efficiency · zero CapEx risk"
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/stories/taffy-town" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/stories">Customer Stories</a><span class="sep">/</span>Taffy Town
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Customer Story · Taffy Town</div>
    <h1>Heavy stacks,<br><em>no risk.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">Taffy Town's manual stacking was the leading source of lift injuries on the floor — and the CapEx required to automate it was the leading reason it hadn't happened. Formic Full Service closed both gaps at once.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/Talos-0143.jpg">
        <source src="/RFA_header.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <span class="dv-fpo">FPO</span>
      <span class="dv-cap">Taffy Town · palletizing cell</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — The Challenge</div>
      <h2>Heavy lifts, <em>real costs</em>.</h2>
      <p>Manual stacking of dense product was Taffy Town's leading source of lifting injuries. Retention suffered — the role was hard to staff, harder to keep staffed. Fixed automation looked like the answer, but the CapEx put it out of reach for years.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Lifting injuries clustered around manual stacking</li>
        <li>High turnover in the role, low retention overall</li>
        <li>CapEx-funded automation outside near-term budget</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0143.jpg" alt="Taffy Town palletizing cell" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Robotic stacking · safe by design</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Haviland_Products_-_Palletizing.gif" alt="Robotic palletizer at Taffy Town" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Full Service · zero CapEx</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — The Solution</div>
      <h2>One system. <em>Zero CapEx.</em></h2>
      <p>Formic deployed a single palletizing cell under the Full Service model. No upfront purchase, no integration risk on Taffy Town, no extra SLA to negotiate. The cell ran in production the same quarter the contract was signed.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>1 palletizing cell deployed under Full Service</li>
        <li>Zero CapEx — fixed monthly fee, all-in</li>
        <li>Integration risk carried by Formic, not Taffy Town</li>
        <li>In production same quarter as contract signing</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:80px;text-align:center">
    <div class="db-tag" style="justify-content:center">03 — The Outcome</div>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:clamp(40px,5vw,72px);font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1;color:var(--white);margin:18px 0 56px">Eliminated injuries. <em style="color:var(--orange);font-style:normal">Zero CapEx risk.</em></h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.1)">
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">1</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Palletizing cell</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">0</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Lifting injuries since</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">$0</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">CapEx outlay</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>End the staffing crisis<br><em>at the end of your line.</em></h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/stories" class="btn-ctawh">More Customer Stories</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
